Protocols/BlueProtocol.html.name: BlueProtocol
Protocols/BlueProtocol.html.abstract: BlueProtocol is used for communication between ViewController and GameScene.

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: botState
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: robot power state 0 = off , 1 = on. This value is updated from the central

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: botAdvertisementData
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: Service Advertisement Data… not important

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: BOT_SERVICE_UUID
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: Service CBUUID

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: BOT_ALERT_INFO_UUID
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: Alert Characsteric CBUUID

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: BOT_ALERT_VALUES
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: robot alerts values [battery, error, stuck, done]. These values when updated, the peripheral will notify the central.

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: BOT_INFO_UUID
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: Bot Info Characsteric CBUUID, read only [status (on/off/stuck/error), battery]

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: BOT_SETTINGS_UUID
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: Settings Characsteric CBUUID, writable [timer, speed]

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: BOT_POWERS_UUID
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: Power Characsteric CBUUID, writable [on / off]

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: peripheralManager
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: CBPeripheralManager instance

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: alertCharacteristics
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: Alert CBMutableCharacteristic instance, needs ref for alerting central

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: gameScene
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: GameScene instance

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: STATUS_OFF
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: Undocumented

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: STATUS_ON
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: Undocumented

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: STATUS_ERROR
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: Undocumented

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: STATUS_STUCK
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: Undocumented

Classes/ViewController.html#/c:@M@BlueBo.name: viewDidLoad()
Classes/ViewController.html#/c:@M@BlueBo.abstract: Init GameScene, PeripheralManager, alertCharacteristics instaces, for more info about viewDidLoad

Classes/ViewController.html#/c:@M@BlueBo.name: peripheralManagerDidUpdateState(_:)
Classes/ViewController.html#/c:@M@BlueBo.abstract: Check the status of the bluetooth. If bluetooth is turned on call prepareService func, for more info about CBPeripheralManager delegate

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: prepareService()
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: Init the robot service and the characteristics and then start advertising

Classes/ViewController.html#/c:@M@BlueBo.name: peripheralManager(_:didReceiveRead:)
Classes/ViewController.html#/c:@M@BlueBo.abstract: Response to read requests by the central, for more info about CBPeripheralManager delegate

Classes/ViewController.html#/c:@M@BlueBo.name: peripheralManager(_:didReceiveWrite:)
Classes/ViewController.html#/c:@M@BlueBo.abstract: Update settings after receiving write request from the central and notifies the central if settings updated correctly or not , for more info about CBPeripheralManager delegate

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: togglePower(data:)
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: Handle the update of the power after receiving write request from the central. This func first convert the data from pointer Data to [UInt8] and then calls GameScene startBot or StopBot functions

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: updateSettings(data:)
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: Handle the update of the settings after receiving write request from the central. This func first convert the data from pointer Data to [UInt8] and then calls GameScene setBotSettings func

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: simulateLowBattery(state:)
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: The implementation of the BlueProtocol protocol which used alert the central that the robot has low battery by updating the first index of BOT_ALERT_VALUES and then calling updateValue

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: simulateStuck(state:)
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: The implementation of the BlueProtocol protocol which used alert the central that the robot is stuck by updating the third index of BOT_ALERT_VALUES and then calling updateValue

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: simulateError(state:)
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: The implementation of the BlueProtocol protocol which used alert the central that the robot has an error and needs restarting by updating the second index of BOT_ALERT_VALUES and then calling updateValue

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: simulateOK()
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: The implementation of the BlueProtocol protocol which used alert the central that the robot is restarted and has no errors by setting all values BOT_ALERT_VALUES to zero and then calling updateValue

Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.name: notifyFinished()
Classes/ViewController.html#/s:7BlueBot1.abstract: The implementation of the BlueProtocol protocol which used alert the central that the robot timer has finishedand updating the last index of BOT_ALERT_VALUES and then calling updateValue

Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.name: distance
Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.abstract: The robot distance per second in pixels

Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.name: bounds
Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.abstract: The bounds where the robot can move

Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.name: barrierSprite
Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.abstract: The barrier sprite used for stuck simulation

Classes/GameScene.html#/c:@M@BlueBot@obj.name: didMove(to:)
Classes/GameScene.html#/c:@M@BlueBot@obj.abstract: Initial the robot sprite, camera, labels and buttons. Also Draw the bounds. For more information about didMove

Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.name: initLabels()
Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.abstract: Initial the headline and four labels on the upper right corner (status, speed, timer, battery )

Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.name: initSimulatorBtns()
Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.abstract: Initial the four buttons on the lower right corner (recharge, Low Battery, Stuck, Error )

Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.name: simulateStuck()
Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.abstract: Triggers stuck state by inserting barrier sprite.

Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.name: simulateError()
Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.abstract: Simulate the error state of the robot

Classes/GameScene.html#/c:@M@BlueBot@obj.name: mouseDown(with:)
Classes/GameScene.html#/c:@M@BlueBot@obj.abstract: capture the mouse click on the buttons to fire the response. For move information about mouseDown

Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.name: setBotSettings(settings:)
Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.abstract: Updates the robot settings (Speed and Timer). This function is called from the ViewController didReceiveWrite func

Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.name: drawBounds()
Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.abstract: Draws black squres that represents the bounds of the room where the robot can move

Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.name: checkBounds()
Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.abstract: Checks of the robot sprite intersects with the bounds and reverse the velocity directions

Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.name: startBot()
Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.abstract: Starts the robot. This function is called from the ViewController togglePower func

Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.name: stopBot()
Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.abstract: Stops the robot. This function is called from the ViewController togglePower func

Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.name: moveBot()
Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.abstract: Move the robot. Called from the Update func

Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.name: checkCollision()
Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.abstract: Checks of the robot sprite intersects with the barrier sprite, call BlueProtocol simulateStuck func to notify the central

Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.name: updateBattery()
Classes/GameScene.html#/s:7BlueBot9GameS.abstract: Update the status of the robot battery

Classes/GameScene.html#/c:@M@BlueBot@obj.name: update(_:)
Classes/GameScene.html#/c:@M@BlueBot@obj.abstract: Performs any scene-specific updates that need to occur before scene actions are evaluated. For more info check update
